	NORTH
	- more industrialized
	- larger population 21.5 million
	- cities are growing
	- transportation growing
	- building railrods and canals
	- developed new technologies
	- workers drive prosperity

	SOUTH
	- more agrarian
	- states rights
	- smaller population 12 million (4 million slaves)
	- Population remaining on farms
	- not changing
	- society based on classes
	- slave labor drives prosperity

ELECTION OF 1848
	Free Soil Party
		do not want slavery to expand into new territory
	Popular Sovereignty
		people in territory decide free or slave
	Zachary Taylor
			presidential nominee for the Whigs	
	California wants statehood
	Taylor dies
		July 9th
	Vice President Millard Fillmore becomes president
	Compromise of 1850
		Stephen Douglas
		California free states
	Fugitive Slave Act
		consequences for assisting runaway slaves
	John C. Calhoun
	Henry and Clay die
	Abolitionists
		majority, loud voice
	Underground Railroad
		helps slaves escape
	
