ELECTION OF 1856
	Candidates
		Republican - John Fremont
		Democratic - James Buchanan
		American-Know-Nothing-Whig - Fillmore
	Buchanan Wins
		wants Kansas as state, Senate denies
	March 1857 Dred Scott Case
		was taken into a free state, meaning he was a free man
		could not sue because he was not a citizen
		property could not be taken wherever wanted
		Missouri Compromise was unconstitutional
		free slaves no longer exist
	
